#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:1
msgid "DMN Orchestration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:3
msgid ""
"The DMN tab enables the editor to go beyond metadata authoring and become an "
"active tool for deploying and testing decision logic. It integrates directly "
"with the Operaton rule engine, which hosts the DMN models that execute "
"government service decisions."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:12
msgid "What the DMN tab does"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:14
msgid ""
"The tab handles the complete lifecycle of a Decision Model and Notation (DMN "
"1.3) file within a service definition:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:16
msgid ""
"**File management.** Upload a `.dmn` file, or load one of the provided "
"examples. The editor parses the DMN XML, extracts all `<decision>` elements, "
"identifies the primary decision key (automatically skipping constant "
"parameters prefixed with `p_*`), and pre-populates the request body with the "
"correct input variable names and types."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:18
msgid ""
"**Syntactic validation.** Immediately after upload, the editor runs the DMN "
"file through the shared backend's five-layer syntactic validator. The result "
"is shown inline in the file card — valid files display a green badge, files "
"with issues display a collapsible panel grouped by layer. See [Syntactic "
"Validation]{1} below."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:20
msgid ""
"**Deployment to Operaton.** Send the DMN file to the configured Operaton "
"engine endpoint via the REST deployment API. Deployment status and ID are "
"tracked and included in the exported Turtle."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:22
msgid ""
"**Live decision evaluation.** Test the deployed model with configurable "
"input variables using a Postman-style interface. The request body is auto-"
"generated but fully editable. Responses are displayed inline."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:24
msgid ""
"**Metadata documentation.** The exported Turtle includes the full DMN "
"metadata: the decision model URI, deployment ID, API endpoint, all input "
"variables as `cpsv:Input` entities, and extracted decision rules with their "
"legal article references as `cprmv:DecisionRule` entities."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:26
msgid ""
"**Import preservation.** When a Turtle file containing DMN data is imported, "
"the DMN blocks are preserved exactly as-is across the import/export cycle. "
"The tab displays a clear notice indicating that the DMN is in imported "
"state, and provides the option to clear and recreate it."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:30
msgid "Syntactic validation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:32
msgid ""
"When a DMN file is uploaded or an example is loaded, the editor "
"automatically calls `POST /v1/dmns/validate` on the shared backend and "
"displays the result in the file card."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:34
msgid ""
"Validation covers five layers. Issues are grouped by layer in a collapsible "
"panel. Each issue carries a severity (error, warning, or informational), a "
"typed code, a human-readable message, and — where applicable — an element "
"reference and line number."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid "Layer"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid "What is checked"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid "**Base DMN**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid ""
"XML well-formedness, root element, DMN namespace, required `<definitions>` "
"attributes, presence of at least one `<decision>`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid "**Business Rules**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid ""
"Hit policy values, `typeRef` on inputs and outputs, rule entry count "
"consistency"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid "**Execution Rules**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid ""
"CPRMV extension attributes — `rulesetType`, `ruleType`, `confidence` enums, "
"ISO date format, BWB ID format, `temporal-period` completeness"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid "**Interaction Rules**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid ""
"`informationRequirement` href resolution, orphaned `<inputData>` elements, "
"variable name consistency"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid "**Content**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:36
msgid ""
"Non-empty CPRMV descriptive attributes, variable `typeRef` presence, non-"
"empty `<textAnnotation>` content"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:44
msgid ""
"A file is considered **valid** when no layer produces an error. Warnings and "
"informational messages do not block deployment — they flag quality "
"improvements recommended for RONL publishing."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:46
msgid ""
"Validation state is cleared when the file is removed via the Clear button, "
"and re-run whenever a new file is loaded."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:48
msgid ""
"For the full specification of every validation code and its rationale, see "
"the [DMN Validation Reference]{1} in the Linked Data Explorer documentation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:52
msgid "Testing capabilities"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:54
msgid ""
"Beyond single-evaluation testing, the DMN tab includes two advanced testing "
"modes:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:56
msgid ""
"**Intermediate decision tests** evaluate each sub-decision in the Decision "
"Requirements Diagram (DRD) individually. This is invaluable for debugging "
"complex multi-table DMNs — rather than examining the final output, you can "
"see exactly which sub-decision is producing an unexpected result. Constant "
"parameters are automatically filtered out; only testable decisions are shown."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:58
msgid ""
"**Test cases** run multiple predefined scenarios from an uploaded JSON file "
"against the primary decision key. Results are displayed progressively — pass/"
"fail counters update in real time as each case executes. Two JSON formats "
"are supported (Toeslagen and DUO format), with automatic normalisation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:60
msgid ""
"A successful test case run also generates NL-SBB concepts for semantic "
"linking via the Linked Data Explorer."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:64
msgid "Smart constant filtering"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cfeatures%5Cdmn-orchestration.md:66
msgid ""
"DMNs for government services frequently contain a large number of constant "
"parameter decisions (prefixed `p_`) alongside the actual decision logic. The "
"editor automatically detects and filters these from the decision key "
"extraction and intermediate test list, so you work with only the testable "
"decisions. The file card shows a badge like \"12 testable decisions detected "
"(p_* constants filtered)\" to make the filtering transparent."
msgstr ""
